x4freetext: PRODUCTION CROSS SECTIONS OF LITHIUM AND BERYLLIUM
ISOTOPES IN C-12 BY HIGH-ENERGY PROTONS AND ALPHA
HIGH PURITY GRAPHITE PIECES: 20*6*1 MM IN SIZE.
FOR PROTON IRRADIATIOS TARGETS CONSISTED IN STACKS OF
10 TO 12 GRAPHITE PIECES WRAPPED IN A 0.02 MM THICK
ALUMINIUM FOIL: THIS ARRANGEMENT CORRESPONDS TO A
TOTAL ENERGY LOSS OF ABOUT 10 MEV AT 155 MEV AND 3 MEV
AT 600 MEV; FOR ALPHA-PARTICLE IRRADIATIONS: ONLY 4
GRAPHITE SLABS WERE USED, MEAN ENERGY OF ALPHA-
PARTICLES IN EACH OF THE FOUR SHEETS WERE 137, 126,
